result.execSummary:
The defendant Major C Latimer was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Major C Latimer is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Major C Latimer was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse, Use of a Dangerous Weapon, Repeater], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Major C Latimer was found guilty of Take/Drive Veh. w/o Consent-Abandon Veh. [Modifiers: Repeater, Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(3m).

Defendant Major C Latimer in court with attorney William Ginsberg. Prosecuting Atty Michael Patrick Finley appeared for State of Wisconsin. Court granted continuance of PH.
